paragraph.tableNote:
Roman letters refer to normal setae, Greek letters to solenidia (except ɛ = famulus). Single prime (
'
) marks setae on anterior and double prime (
"
) setae on posterior side of the given leg segment. Parentheses refer to a pair of setae. Tr – trochanter, Fe – femur, Ge – genu, Ti – Tibia, Ta – tarsus.
